ats_analysis.issue: Insecure communication to apollo-1-fe-int.mycompany.hu is allowed
ats_analysis.description: NSExceptionAllowsInsecureHTTPLoads allows insecure HTTP loads to apollo-1-fe-int.mycompany.hu, or to be able to loosen the server trust evaluation requirements for HTTPS connections to the domain.

ats_analysis.issue: NSExceptionRequiresForwardSecrecy set to NO for apollo-1-fe-int.mycompany.hu
ats_analysis.description: NSExceptionRequiresForwardSecrecy limits the accepted ciphers to those that support perfect forward secrecy (PFS) through the Elliptic Curve Diffie-Hellman Ephemeral (ECDHE) key exchange. Set the value for this key to NO to override the requirement that a server must support PFS for the given domain. This key is optional. The default value is YES, which limits the accepted ciphers to those that support PFS through Elliptic Curve Diffie-Hellman Ephemeral (ECDHE) key exchange.

ats_analysis.issue: NSIncludesSubdomains set to TRUE for hu.srv.acc.sys
ats_analysis.description: NSIncludesSubdomains applies the ATS exceptions for the given domain to all subdomains as well. For example, the ATS exceptions in the domain exception dictionary apply to hu.srv.acc.sys, as well as math.hu.srv.acc.sys, history.hu.srv.acc.sys, and so on. Otherwise, if the value is NO, the exceptions apply only to hu.srv.acc.sys.

ats_analysis.issue: NSExceptionRequiresForwardSecrecy set to NO for hu.srv.acc.sys
ats_analysis.description: NSExceptionRequiresForwardSecrecy limits the accepted ciphers to those that support perfect forward secrecy (PFS) through the Elliptic Curve Diffie-Hellman Ephemeral (ECDHE) key exchange. Set the value for this key to NO to override the requirement that a server must support PFS for the given domain. This key is optional. The default value is YES, which limits the accepted ciphers to those that support PFS through Elliptic Curve Diffie-Hellman Ephemeral (ECDHE) key exchange.
